tes are disabled.'=>'Security rules updates are disabled.','Various options'=>'Various options','This message will be displayed above the captcha. Max. 255 characters.'=>'This message will be displayed above the captcha. Max. 255 characters.','Enable protection'=>'Enable protection','Type of protection'=>'Type of protection','Error: GD Support is not available on your server, the captcha protection will not work!'=>'Error: GD Support is not available on your server, the captcha protection will not work!','Type the characters you see in the picture below:'=>'Type the characters you see in the picture below:','substitution character:'=>'substitution character:','NinjaFirewall will attempt to block bots and scripts immediately, i.e., even before they start a brute-force attack.'=>'NinjaFirewall will attempt to block bots and scripts immediately, i.e., even before they start a brute-force attack.','Bot protection:'=>'Bot protection:','<b>Captcha:</b> It will display a 5-character captcha code.'=>'<b>Captcha:</b> It will display a 5-character captcha code.','<b>Password:</b> It password-protects the login page. NinjaFirewall uses its own very fast authentication scheme and it is compatible with any HTTP server (Apache, Nginx, Lighttpd etc).'=>'<b>Password:</b> It password-protects the login page. NinjaFirewall uses its own very fast authentication scheme and it is compatible with any HTTP server (Apache, Nginx, Lighttpd etc).','Type of protection:'=>'Type of protection:','NinjaFirewall will always enforce the HTTP authentication or captcha implementation each time you access the login page.'=>'NinjaFirewall will always enforce the HTTP authentication or captcha implementation each time you access the login page.','The protection will be triggered when too many login attempts are detected, regardless of the offending IP. It blocks the attack instantly and prevents it from reaching WordPress, but still allows you to access your administration console using either the predefined username/password combination or the captcha code.'=>'The protection will be triggered when too many login attempts are detected, regardless of the offending IP. It blocks the attack instantly and prevents it from reaching WordPress, but still allows you to access your administration console using, either the predefined username/password combination, or the captcha code.','You can choose two different types of protection: a password or a captcha. You can enable the protection only if an attack is detected or to keep it always activated.'=>'You can choose two different types of protection: a password or a captcha. You can enable the protection only if an attack is detected or to keep it always activated.','Message (max. 1024 characters, HTML tags allowed)'=>'Message (max. 1024 characters, HTML tags allowed)','Please enter max 1024 character only.'=>'Please enter max 1024 character only.','NinjaFirewall is not compatible with Microsoft Windows.'=>'NinjaFirewall is not compatible with Microsoft Windows.','This option will reject any <code>GET</code> or <code>POST</code> request, <code>HTTP_USER_AGENT</code>, <code>HTTP_REFERER</code> variables containing ASCII characters from 1 to 8 and 14 to 31.'=>'This option will reject any <code>GET</code> or <code>POST</code> request, <code>HTTP_USER_AGENT</code>, <code>HTTP_REFERER</code> variables containing ASCII characters from 1 to 8 and 14 to 31.','PHP has several wrappers for use with the filesystem functions. It is possible for an attacker to use them to bypass firewalls and various IDS to exploit remote and local file inclusions. This option lets you block any script attempting to pass a <code>expect://</code>, <code>file://</code>, <code>phar://</code>, <code>php://</code>, <code>zip://</code> or <code>data://</code> stream inside a <code>GET</code> or <code>POST</code> request, cookies, user agent and referrer variables.'=>'PHP has several wrappers for use with the filesystem functions. It is possible for an attacker to use them to bypass firewalls and various IDS to exploit remote and local file inclusions. This option lets you block any script attempting to pass a <code>expect://</code>, <code>file://</code>, <code>phar://</code>, <code>php://</code>, <code>zip://</code> or <code>data://</code> stream inside a <code>GET</code> or <code>POST</code> request, cookies, user agent and referrer variables.','Error: Wrong rules format.'=>'Error: Wrong rules format.','Full or partial case-sensitive string(s), max. 255 characters. Multiple values must be comma-separated'=>'Full or partial case-sensitive string(s), max. 255 characters. Multiple values must be comma-separated','WordPress REST API'=>'WordPress REST API','Through the WordPress REST API'=>'Through the WordPress REST API','Block serialized PHP objects'=>'Block serialised PHP objects','NinjaFirewall is running in %s mode.'=>'NinjaFirewall is running in %s mode.','Mode'=>'Mode','Username:'=>'Username:','Blocked privilege escalation attempt'=>'Blocked privilege escalation attempt','Forbidden access'=>'Forbidden access','WordPress WAF mode'=>'WordPress WAF mode','Full WAF mode'=>'Full WAF mode','It allows you to access your WordPress site\'s data through an easy-to-use HTTP REST API. Since WordPress 4.7, it is enabled by default. NinjaFirewall allows you to block any access to that API if you do not intend to use it.'=>'It allows you to access your WordPress site\'s data through an easy-to-use HTTP REST API. Since WordPress 4.7, it is enabled by default. NinjaFirewall allows you to block any access to that API if you do not intend to use it.','It is possible to enumerate usernames either through the WordPress author archives, author sitemap, the REST API or the login page. Although this is not a vulnerability but a WordPress feature, some hackers use it to retrieve usernames in order to launch more accurate brute-force attacks. If it is a failed login attempt, NinjaFirewall will sanitise the error message returned by WordPress. If it is an author archives scan, it will invalidate it and redirect the user to the blog index page. Regarding the WP REST API, it will block the request immediately.'=>'It is possible to enumerate usernames either through the WordPress author archives, author sitemap, the REST API or the login page. Although this is not a vulnerability but a WordPress feature, some hackers use it to retrieve usernames in order to launch more accurate brute-force attacks. If it is a failed login attempt, NinjaFirewall will sanitise the error message returned by WordPress. If it is an author archives scan, it will invalidate it and redirect the user to the blog index page. Regarding the WP REST API, it will block the request immediately.','Object Serialization is a PHP feature used by many applications to generate a storable representation of a value. However, some insecure PHP applications and plugins can turn that feature into a critical vulnerability called <a href="%s">PHP Object Injection</a>. This option can block serialized PHP objects found inside a a <code>GET</code> or <code>POST</code> request, cookies, user agent and referrer variables.'=>'Object Serialisation is a PHP feature used by many applications to generate a storable representation of a value. However, some insecure PHP applications and plugins can turn that feature into a critical vulnerability called <a href="%s">PHP Object Injection</a>. This option can block serialised PHP objects found inside a a <code>GET</code> or <code>POST</code> request, cookies, user agent and referrer variables.','Block Pingbacks'=>'Block Pingbacks','XML-RPC is a remote procedure call (RPC) protocol which uses XML to encode its calls and HTTP as a transport mechanism. WordPress has an XMLRPC API that can be accessed through the <code>xmlrpc.php</code> file. Since WordPress version 3.5, it is always activated and cannot be turned off. NinjaFirewall allows you to immediately block any access to that file, or only to block an access using the <code>system.multicall</code> method often used in brute-force amplification attacks or to block Pingbacks.'=>'XML-RPC is a remote procedure call (RPC) protocol which uses XML to encode its calls and HTTP as a transport mechanism. WordPress has an XMLRPC API that can be accessed through the <code>xmlrpc.php</code> file. Since WordPress version 3.5, it is always activated and cannot be turned off. NinjaFirewall allows you to immediately block any access to that file, or only to block an access using the <code>system.multicall</code> method often used in brute-force amplification attacks or to block Pingbacks.','NinjaFirewall brute-force protection is enabled and you are temporarily whitelisted.'=>'NinjaFirewall brute-force protection is enabled and you are temporarily whitelisted.','This CSP header will apply to the WordPress admin dashboard only.'=>'This CSP header will apply to the WordPress admin dashboard only.','Set %s for the WordPress admin dashboard'=>'Set %s for the WordPress admin dashboard','This CSP header will apply to the website frontend only.'=>'This CSP header will apply to the website front-end only.','Set %s for the website frontend'=>'Set %s for the website front-end','Error: %s'=>'Error: %s','the whitelisted IP is not valid. Please <a href="%s">check your configuration</a>.'=>'the whitelisted IP is not valid. Please <a href="%s">check your configuration</a>.','IP address %s is allowed to access NinjaFirewall\'s log on this server.'=>'IP address %s is allowed to access NinjaFirewall\'s log on this server.','No IP address restriction.'=>'No IP address restriction.','the public key is invalid. Please <a href="%s">check your configuration</a>.'=>'the public key is invalid. Please <a href="%s">check your configuration</a>.','There is no limit to the number of websites you can connect to, and they can be running any edition of NinjaFirewall: WP, <font color="#21759B">WP+</font>, Pro or <font color="red">Pro+</font>.'=>'There is no limit to the