ptions','Scan System For File Changes'=>'Scan System For File Changes','None'=>'None','New'=>'New','Old'=>'Old','Modified files:'=>'Modified files:','Deleted files:'=>'Deleted files:','Change'=>'Change','Uid / Gid'=>'Uid / Gid','Access'=>'Access','Size'=>'Size','New files:'=>'New files:','Click a file to get more info about it.'=>'Click a file to get more info about it.','Download Changes'=>'Download Changes','View Changes'=>'View Changes','Modified files: %s'=>'Modified files: %s','Deleted files: %s'=>'Deleted files: %s','New files: %s'=>'New files: %s','Last changes'=>'Last changes','Delete Snapshot'=>'Delete Snapshot','Download Snapshot'=>'Download Snapshot','Processing time: %s seconds'=>'Processing time: %s seconds','do not follow'=>'do not follow','follow'=>'follow','Symlinks:'=>'Symlinks:','Exclusion:'=>'Exclusion:','Directory:'=>'Directory:','Total files: %s '=>'Total files: %s ','Created on: %s'=>'Created on: %s','Last snapshot'=>'Last snapshot','Delete the current snapshot ?'=>'Delete the current snapshot?','Create Snapshot'=>'Create Snapshot','Do not follow symbolic links (default)'=>'Do not follow symbolic links (default)','Full or partial case-sensitive string(s). Multiple values must be comma-separated'=>'Full or partial case-sensitive string(s). Multiple values must be comma-separated','e.g.,'=>'e.g.,','Create a snapshot of all files stored in that directory'=>'Create a snapshot of all files stored in that directory','No changes detected.'=>'No changes detected.','NinjaFirewall detected that changes were made to your files.'=>'NinjaFirewall detected that changes were made to your files.','You must create a snapshot first.'=>'You must create a snapshot first.','Snapshot file successfully deleted.'=>'Snapshot file successfully deleted.','Snapshot successfully created.'=>'Snapshot successfully created.','Support forum:'=>'Support forum:','This notification can be turned off from NinjaFirewall "Event Notifications" page.'=>'This notification can be turned off from the NinjaFirewall "Event Notifications" page.','Blocked brute-force attacks:'=>'Blocked brute-force attacks:','medium:'=>'medium:','high:'=>'high:','critical:'=>'critical:','Date Range Processed: Yesterday'=>'Date Range Processed: Yesterday','Daily activity report for: %s'=>'Daily activity report for: %s','[NinjaFirewall] Daily Activity Report'=>'[NinjaFirewall] Daily Activity Report','Save Event Notifications'=>'Save Event Notifications','Other(s):'=>'Other(s):','To the administrator of the site where originated the alert'=>'To the administrator of the site where the alert originated','Only to me, the Super Admin'=>'Only to me, the Super Admin','Multiple recipients must be comma-separated (e.g., <code>joe@example.org,alice@example.org</code>).'=>'Multiple recipients must be comma-separated (e.g., <code>joe@example.org,alice@example.org</code>).','Alerts should be sent to'=>'Alerts should be sent to','Contact email'=>'Contact email','Write all events to the firewall log'=>'Write all events to the firewall log','Log'=>'Log','Send me a daily activity report'=>'Send me a daily activity report','Daily report'=>'Daily report','An administrator account is created, modified or deleted in the database (default)'=>'An administrator account is created, modified or deleted in the database (default)','Updates WordPress (default)'=>'Updates WordPress (default)','Core'=>'Core','Deletes a theme'=>'Deletes a theme','Activates a theme'=>'Activates a theme','Installs a theme (default)'=>'Installs a theme (default)','Uploads a theme (default)'=>'Uploads a theme (default)','Themes'=>'Themes','Deletes a plugin'=>'Deletes a plugin','Deactivates a plugin (default)'=>'Deactivates a plugin (default)','Updates a plugin'=>'Updates a plugin','Activates a plugin'=>'Activates a plugin','Installs a plugin (default)'=>'Installs a plugin (default)','Uploads a plugin (default)'=>'Uploads a plugin (default)','Send me an alert whenever someone'=>'Send me an alert whenever someone','Plugins'=>'Plugins','No, thanks (not recommended)'=>'No, thanks. (not recommended)','Someone - user, admin, editor, etc - logs in'=>'Someone - user, admin, editor, etc. - logs in','An administrator logs in (default)'=>'An administrator logs in (default)','Send me an alert whenever'=>'Send me an alert whenever','WordPress admin dashboard'=>'WordPress admin dashboard','Your changes have been saved.'=>'Your changes have been saved.','I want to make the changes myself.'=>'I want to make the changes myself.','Let NinjaFirewall make the necessary changes (recommended).'=>'Let NinjaFirewall make the necessary changes (recommended).','The %s file must be created, and the following lines of code added to it:'=>'The %s file must be created, and the following lines of code added to it:','Select the PHP initialization file supported by your server'=>'Select the PHP initialisation file supported by your server','View PHPINFO'=>'View PHPINFO','Select your HTTP server and your PHP server API'=>'Select your HTTP server and your PHP server API','(recommended)'=>'(recommended)','NinjaFirewall (WP Edition)'=>'NinjaFirewall (WP Edition)','NinjaFirewall cannot create its <code>nfwlog/</code>log and cache folder; please make sure that the <code>%s</code> directory is writable'=>'NinjaFirewall cannot create its <code>nfwlog/</code>log and cache folder. Please make sure that the <code>%s</code> directory is writable','License'=>'Licence','Thank you for using NinjaFirewall.'=>'Thank you for using NinjaFirewall.','We recommend to enable this feature, as it is the <strong>best way to keep your WordPress secure</strong> against new vulnerabilities.'=>'We recommend enabling this feature, as it is the <strong>best way to keep your WordPress secure</strong> against new vulnerabilities.','Only security rules will be downloaded. If a new version of NinjaFirewall (including new files, options and features) was available, it would have to be updated from the dashboard plugins menu as usual.'=>'Only security rules will be downloaded. If a new version of NinjaFirewall (including new files, options and features) were available, it would have to be updated from the dashboard plugins menu as usual.','To get the most efficient protection, you can ask NinjaFirewall to automatically update its security rules.'=>'To get the most efficient protection, you can ask NinjaFirewall to automatically update its security rules.','Updates'=>'Updates','Note: if the <code>RULE</code> column from your log shows a hyphen <code>-</code> instead of a number, that means that the rule can be changed in the "Firewall Policies" page.'=>'Note: if the <code>RULE</code> column from your log shows a hyphen <code>-</code> instead of a number, that means that the rule can be changed in the "Firewall Policies" page.','Select its ID from the enabled rules list below and click the "Disable it" button.'=>'Select its ID from the enabled rules list below and click the "Disable it" button.','Check your firewall log and find the rule ID you want to disable (it is displayed in the <code>RULE</code> column).'=>'Check your firewall log and find the rule ID you want to disable (it is displayed in the <code>RULE</code> column).','Besides the "Firewall Policies", NinjaFirewall includes also a large set of built-in rules used to protect your blog against the most common vulnerabilities and hacking attempts. They are always enabled and you cannot edit them, but if you notice that your visitors are wrongly blocked by some of those rules, you can use the Rules Editor below to disable them individually:'=>'Besides the "Firewall Policies", NinjaFirewall includes also a large set of built-in rules used to protect your blog against the most common vulnerabilities and hacking attempts. They are always enabled and you cannot edit them, but if you notice that your visitors are wrongly blocked by some of those rules, you can use the Rules Editor below to disable them individually:','Rules Editor'=>'Rules Editor','Additionally, you can include any of the following characters: <code>"</code>, <code>%</code>, <code>[</code>, <code>]</code>, <code>space</code> and lowercase letters <code>a-z</code>.'=>'Additionally, you can include any of the following characters: <code>"</code>, <code>%</code>, <code>[</code>, <code>]</code>, <code>space</code> and lowercase letters <code>a-z</code>.','<code>%host</code>: the requested host (HTTP_HOST), if any.'=>'<code>%host</code>: the requested host (HTTP_HOST), if any.','<code>%forward</code>: HTTP_X_FORWARDED_FOR, if any. If you are behind a load balancer or CDN, this will likely be the visitor true IP.'=>'<code>%forward</code>: HTTP_X_FORWARDED_FOR, if any. If you are behind a load balancer or CDN, this will likely be the visitor\'s true IP.','<code>%ua</code>: the user-agent (HTTP_USER_AGENT), if any.'=>'<code>%ua</code>: the user-agent (HTTP_USER_AGENT), if any.','<code>%referrer</code>: the referrer (HTTP_REFERER), if any.'=>'<code>%referrer</code>: the referrer (HTTP_REFERER), if any.','<code>%uri</code>: the URI which was given in order to access the page (REQUEST_URI).'=>'<code>%uri</code>: the URI which was given in order to access the page (REQUEST_URI).','<code>%method</code>: HTTP method (e.g., GET, POST).'=>'<code>%method</code>: HTTP method (e.g., GET, POST).','<code>%client</code>: the client REMOTE_ADDR. If you are behind a load balancer or CDN, this will be its IP.'=>'<code>%client</code>: the client REMOTE_ADDR. If you are behind a load balancer or CDN, this will be its IP.','<code>%name</code>: authenticated user (HTTP basic auth), if any.'=>'<code>%name</code>: authenticated user (HTTP basic auth), if any.','<code>%time</code>: the server date, time and timezone.'=>'<code>%time</code>: the server date, time and timezone.','You can easily customize the log format. Possible values are:'=>'You can easily customise the log format. Possible values are:','Log Format'=>'Log Format','If you are using the optional <code>.htninja</code> configuration file to whitelist your IP, the Live Log feature will not work.'=>'If you are using the optional <code>.htninja</code> configuration file to whitelist your IP, the Live Log feature will not work.','Live Log does not make use of any WordPress core file (e.g., <code>admin-ajax.php</code>). It communicates directly with the firewall without loading WordPress bootstrap. Consequently, it is fast, lightweight and it should not affect your server load, even if you set its refresh rate to the lowest value.'=>'Live Log does not make use of any WordPress core file (eg <code>admin-ajax.php</code>). It communicates directly with the firewall without loading the WordPress bootstrap. Consequently, it is fast, lightweight, and it should not affect your server load, even if you set its refresh rate to the lowest value.','You can enable/disable the monitoring process, change the refresh rate, clear the screen, enable automatic vertical scrolling, change the log format, select which traffic you want to view (HTTP/HTTPS) and the timezone.'=>'You can enable/disable the monitoring process, change the refresh rate, clear the screen, enable automatic vertical scrolling, change the log format, select which traffic you want to view (HTTP/HTTPS), and the time zone.','Live Log'=>'Live Log','REQUEST : the HTTP request including offending variables and values as well as the reason the action was logged.'=>'REQUEST : the HTTP request, including the offending variables and values, as well as the reason the action was logged.','RULE : reference of the NinjaFirewall built-in security rule that triggered the action. A hyphen (<code>-</code>) instead of a number means it was a rule from the "Firewall Policies" page.'=>'RULE : reference of the NinjaFirewall built-in security rule that triggered the action. A hyphen (<code>-</code>) instead of a number means it was a rule from the "Firewall Policies" page.','LEVEL : level of severity (<code>CRITICAL</code>, <code>HIGH</code> or <code>MEDIUM</code>), information (<code>INFO</code>, <code>UPLOAD</code>) and debugging mode (<code>DEBUG_ON</code>).'=>'LEVEL : level of severity (<code>CRITICAL</code>, <code>HIGH</code> or <code>MEDIUM</code>), information (<code>INFO</code>, <code>UPLOAD</code>) and debugging mode (<code>DEBUG_ON</code>).','INCIDENT : unique incident number/ID as it was displayed to the blocked user.'=>'INCIDENT : unique incident number/ID as it was displayed to the blocked user.','DATE : date and time of the incident.'=>'DATE : date and time of the incident.','The firewall log displays blocked and sanitised requests as well as some useful information. It has 6  columns:'=>'The firewall log displays blocked and sanitised requests, as well as some useful information. It has 6 columns:','Firewall Log'=>'Firewall Log','Be careful if you are behind a load balancer, reverse-proxy or CDN because the Login Protection feature will always record the <code>REMOTE_ADDR</code> IP. If you have an application parsing the AUTH log in order to ban IPs (e.g. Fail2ban), you <strong>must</strong> setup your HTTP server to forward the correct IP (or use the <code><a href="%s">.htninja</a></code> file), otherwise you will likely block legitimate users.'=>'Be careful if you are behind a load balancer, reverse-proxy or CDN because the Login Protection feature will always record the <code>REMOTE_ADDR</code> IP. If you have an application parsing the AUTH log in order to ban IPs (e.g. Fail2ban), you <strong>must</strong> setup your HTTP server to forward the correct IP (or use the <code><a href="%s">.htninja</a></code> file), otherwise you will likely block legitimate users.','Sample loglines:'=>'Sample loglines:','EE: the time, in minutes, the protection will remain active.'=>'EE: the time, in minutes, the protection will remain active.','DD: the target: it can be either <code>wp-login.php</code> or <code>XML-RPC API</code>.'=>'DD: the target: it can be either <code>wp-login.php</code> or <code>XML-RPC API</code>.','CC: the blog (sub-)domain name.'=>'CC: the blog (sub-)domain name.','AA: the process ID (PID).'=>'AA: the process ID (PID).','On Debian-based systems, the log is located in <code>/var/log/auth.log</code>, and on Red Hat-based systems in <code>/var/log/secure</code>. The logline uses the following format:'=>'On Debian-based systems, the log is located in <code>/var/log/auth.log</code>, and on Red Hat-based systems in <code>/var/log/secure</code>. The logline uses the following format:','If you have a shared hosting account, keep this option disabled as you do not have any access to the server\'s logs.'=>'If you have a shared hosting account, keep this option disabled as you do not have any access to the server\'s logs.','NinjaFirewall can write to the server Authentication log when the brute-force protection is triggered. This can be useful to the system administrator for monitoring purposes or banning IPs at the server level.'=>'NinjaFirewall can write to the server Authentication log when the brute-force protection is triggered. This can be useful to the system administrator for monitoring purposes or banning IPs at the server level.','AUTH log'=>'AUTH log','Always ON:'=>'Always ON:','Message'=>'Message','Yes, if under attack:'=>'Yes, if under attack:','By processing incoming HTTP requests before your blog and any of its plugins, NinjaFirewall is the only plugin for WordPress able to protect it against very large brute-force attacks, including distributed attacks coming from several thousands of different IPs.'=>'By processing incoming HTTP requests before your blog and any of its plugins, NinjaFirewall is the only plugin for WordPress that is able to protect it against very large brute-force attacks, including distributed attacks coming from several thousands of different IPs.','Login Protection'=>'Login Protection','NinjaFirewall can alert you by email on specific events triggered within your blog. They include installations, updates, activations etc, as well as users login and modification of any administrator account in the database. Some of those alerts are enabled by default and it is highly recommended to keep them enabled. It is not unusual for a hacker, after breaking into your WordPress admin console, to install or just to upload a backdoored plugin or theme in order to take full control of your website.'=>'NinjaFirewall can alert you by email of specific events triggered within your blog. They include installations, updates, activations, etc., as well as user logins and the modification of any administrator account in the database. Some of those alerts are enabled by default and it is highly recommended to keep them enabled. It is not unusual for a hacker, after breaking into your WordPress admin console, to install or just to upload a backdoored plugin or theme in order to take full control of your website.','Event Notifications'=>'Event Notifications','Scheduled scans rely on <a href="%s">WordPress pseudo cron</a> which works only if your site gets sufficient traffic.'=>'Scheduled scans rely on <a href="%s">WordPress pseudo cron</a> which works only if your site gets sufficient traffic.','Reports will be sent to the contact email address defined in the "Event Notifications" menu.'=>'Reports will be sent to the contact email address defined in the "Event Notifications" menu.','It can either send you a scan report only if changes are detected, or always send you one after each scan.'=>'It can either send you a scan report only if changes are detected, or always send you one after each scan.','NinjaFirewall can scan your system on a specific interval (hourly, twicedaily or daily).'=>'NinjaFirewall can scan your system on a specific interval (hourly, twicedaily or daily).','Scheduled scans'=>'Scheduled scans','Do not follow symbolic links: by default, NinjaFirewall will not follow symbolic links.'=>'Do not follow symbolic links: by default, NinjaFirewall will not follow symbolic links.','Multiple values must be comma-separated (e.g., <code>/foo/bar/,.css,.png</code>).'=>'Multiple values must be comma-separated (e.g., <code>/foo/bar/,.css,.png</code>).','Exclude the following files/folders: you can enter a directory or a file name (e.g., <code>/foo/bar/</code>), or a part of it (e.g., <code>foo</code>). Or you can exclude a file extension (e.g., <code>.css</code>).'=>'Exclude the following files/folders: you can enter a directory or a file name (e.g., <code>/foo/bar/</code>), or a part of it (e.g., <code>foo</code>). Or you can exclude a file extension (e.g., <code>.css</code>).','Create a snapshot of all files stored in that directory: by default, the directory is set to WordPress <code>ABSPATH</code> (%s)'=>'Create a snapshot of all files stored in that directory: by default, the directory is set to WordPress <code>ABSPATH</code> (%s)','You need to create a snapshot of all your files and then, at a later time, you can scan your system to compare it with the previous snapshot. Any modification will be immediately detected: file content, file permissions, file ownership, timestamp as well as file creation and deletion.'=>'You need to create a snapshot of all your files and then, at a later time, you can scan your system to compare it with the previous snapshot. Any modification will be immediately detected: file content, file permissions, file ownership, timestamp as well as file creation and deletion.','File Check lets you perform file integrity monitoring upon request or on a specific interval.'=>'File Check lets you perform file integrity monitoring upon request or on a specific interval.','File Check'=>'File Check','Note that when it is disabled, the icon still remains visible to you, the Super Admin.'=>'Note that when it is disabled, the icon still remains visible to you, the Super Admin.','It is recommended to enable this feature as it is the only way to know whether the sites in your network are protected and if NinjaFirewall installation was successful.'=>'It is recommended to enable this feature as it is the only way to know whether the sites in your network are protected and if the NinjaFirewall installation was successful.','Even if NinjaFirewall administration menu is only available to the Super Admin (from the main site), you can still display its status to all sites in the network by adding a small NinjaFirewall icon to their WordPress ToolBar. It will be visible only to the administrators of those sites.'=>'Even if the NinjaFirewall administration menu is only available to the Super Admin (from the main site), you can still display its status to all sites in the network by adding a small NinjaFirewall icon to their WordPress ToolBar. It will be visible only to the administrators of those sites.','Network'=>'Network','File Guard real-time detection is a totally unique feature, because NinjaFirewall is the only plugin for WordPress that can hook HTTP requests sent to any PHP script, even if that script is not part of the WordPress package (third-party software, shell script, backdoor etc).'=>'File Guard real-time detection is a totally unique feature, because NinjaFirewall is the only plugin for WordPress that can hook HTTP requests sent to any PHP script, even if that script is not part of the WordPress package (third-party software, shell script, backdoor etc).','If you do not want to monitor a folder, you can exclude its full path or a part of it (e.g., <code>/var/www/public_html/cache/</code> or <code>/cache/</code> etc). NinjaFirewall will compare this value to the <code>$_SERVER["SCRIPT_FILENAME"]</code> server variable and, if it matches, will ignore it.'=>'If you do not want to monitor a folder, you can exclude its full path or a part of it (e.g., <code>/var/www/public_html/cache/</code> or <code>/cache/</code> etc). NinjaFirewall will compare this value to the <code>$_SERVER["SCRIPT_FILENAME"]</code> server variable and, if it matches, will ignore it.','If a hacker uploaded a shell script to your site (or injected a backdoor into an already existing file) and tried to directly access that file using his browser or a script, NinjaFirewall would hook the HTTP request and immediately detect that the file was recently modified/created. It would send you a detailed alert (script name, IP, request, date and time). Alerts will be sent to the contact email address defined in the "Event Notifications" menu.'=>'If a hacker uploaded a shell script to your site (or injected a backdoor into an already existing file) and tried to directly access that file using his browser or a script, NinjaFirewall would hook the HTTP request and immediately detect that the file was recently modified/created. It would send you a detailed alert (script name, IP, request, date and time). Alerts will be sent to the contact email address defined in the "Event Notifications" menu.','File Guard can detect, in real-time, any access to a PHP file that was recently modified or created, and alert you about this.'=>'File Guard can detect, in real-time, any access to a PHP file that was recently modified or created, and alert you about this.','File Guard'=>'File Guard','This option will block users being able to use the plugin and theme installation/update functionality from the WordPress admin area. Setting this constant also disables the Plugin and Theme editor.'=>'This option will block users being able to use the plugin and theme installation/update functionality from the WordPress admin area. Setting this constant also disables the Plugin and Theme editor.','Disable plugin and theme update/installation <code>DISALLOW_FILE_MODS</code>'=>'Disable plugin and theme update/installation <code>DISALLOW_FILE_MODS</code>','Disabling the plugin and theme editor provides an additional layer of security if a hacker gains access to a well-privileged user account.'=>'Disabling the plugin and theme editor provides an additional layer of security if a hacker gains access to a well-privileged user account.','Disable the plugin and theme editor <code>DISALLOW_FILE_EDIT</code>'=>'Disable the plugin and theme editor <code>DISALLOW_FILE_EDIT</code>','Enable this option when you want to secure logins and the admin area so that both passwords and cookies are never sent in the clear. Ensure that you can access your admin console from HTTPS before enabling this option, otherwise you will lock yourself out of your site!'=>'Enable this option when you want to secure logins and the admin area, so that both passwords and cookies are never sent in the clear. Ensure that you can access your admin console from HTTPS before enabling this option, otherwise you will lock yourself out of your site!','Force HTTPS for admin and logins <code>FORCE_SSL_ADMIN</code>'=>'Force HTTPS for admin and logins <code>FORCE_SSL_ADMIN</code>','This option can be useful to block hackers from installing backdoor in the PHP theme files. However, because some custom themes may include an HTML form (contact, search form etc), this option is not enabled by default.'=>'This option can be useful to block hackers from backdoor installing in the PHP theme files. However, because some custom themes may include an HTML form (contact, search form, etc), this option is not enabled by default.','Block <code>POST</code> requests in the themes folder <code>/wp-content/themes</code>'=>'Block <code>POST</code> requests in the themes folder <code>/wp-content/themes</code>','Whether to block direct access to PHP files located in specific WordPress directories.'=>'Whether to block direct access to PHP files located in specific WordPress directories.','This option will reject any <code>GET</code> or <code>POST</code> request, <code>HTTP_USER_AGENT</code>, <code>REQUEST_URI</code>, <code>PHP_SELF</code>, <code>PATH_INFO</code>, <code>HTTP_REFERER</code> variables containing the ASCII character 0x00 (NULL byte). Such a character is dangerous and should always be rejected.'=>'This option will reject any <code>GET</code> or <code>POST</code> request, <code>HTTP_USER_AGENT</code>, <code>REQUEST_URI</code>, <code>PHP_SELF</code>, <code>PATH_INFO</code>, <code>HTTP_REFERER</code> variables containing the ASCII character 0x00 (NULL byte). Such a character is dangerous and should always be rejected.','This option will block scripts attempting to pass the <code>DOCUMENT_ROOT</code> server variable in a <code>GET</code> or <code>POST</code> request. Hackers use shell scripts that often need to pass this value, but most legitimate programs do not.'=>'This option will block scripts attempting to pass the <code>DOCUMENT_ROOT</code> server variable in a <code>GET</code> or <code>POST</code> request. Hackers use shell scripts that often need to pass this value, but most legitimate programs do not.','Block the <code>DOCUMENT_ROOT</code> server variable (%s) in HTTP requests'=>'Block the <code>DOCUMENT_ROOT</code> server variable (%s) in HTTP requests','Various'=>'Various','This option can sanitise any dangerous characters found in those 3 server variables to prevent various XSS and database injection attempts.'=>'This option can sanitise any dangerous characters found in those three server variables to prevent various XSS and database injection attempts.','Sanitise <code>PHP_SELF</code>, <code>PATH_TRANSLATED</code>, <code>PATH_INFO</code>'=>'Sanitise <code>PHP_SELF</code>, <code>PATH_TRANSLATED</code>, <code>PATH_INFO</code>','This option lets you hide errors returned by your scripts. Such errors can leak sensitive informations which can be exploited by hackers.'=>'This option lets you hide errors returned by your scripts. Such errors can leak sensitive information, which can be exploited by hackers.','this option will allow the firewall to scan traffic from all non-routable private IPs (IPv4 and IPv6) as well as the localhost IP. We recommend to keep it enabled if you have a private network (2 or more servers interconnected).'=>'this option will allow the firewall to scan traffic from all non-routable private IPs (IPv4 and IPv6) as well as the localhost IP. We recommend to keep it enabled if you have a private network (2 or more servers interconnected).','This option will reject any request using an IP instead of a domain name in the <code>Host</code> header of the HTTP request. Unless you need to connect to your site using its IP address, (e.g. %s), enabling this option will block a lot of hackers scanners because such applications scan IPs rather than domain names.'=>'This option will reject any request using an IP instead of a domain name in the <code>Host</code> header of the HTTP request. Unless you need to connect to your site using its IP address, (eg %s), enabling this option will block a lot of hackers\' scanners, because such applications scan IPs rather than domain names.','this option will block any <code>GET</code> or <code>POST</code> request containing the localhost IP (127.0.0.1). It can be useful to block SQL dumpers and various hacker\'s shell scripts.'=>'this option will block any <code>GET</code> or <code>POST</code> request containing the localhost IP (127.0.0.1). It can be useful to block SQL dumpers and various hacker\'s shell scripts.','Block localhost IP in <code>GET/POST</code> requests'=>'Block localhost IP in <code>GET/POST</code> requests','This policy enforces secure HTTPS connections to the server. Web browsers will not allow the user to access the web application over insecure HTTP protocol. It helps to defend against cookie hijacking and Man-in-the-middle attacks. Most recent browsers support HSTS headers.'=>'This policy enforces secure HTTPS connections to the server. Web browsers will not allow the user to access the web application over insecure HTTP protocol. It helps to defend against cookie hijacking and man-in-the-middle attacks. Most recent browsers support HSTS headers.','Set <code>Strict-Transport-Security</code> (HSTS) to enforce secure connections to the server'=>'Set <code>Strict-Transport-Security</code> (HSTS) to enforce secure connections to the server','If your PHP scripts send cookies that need to be accessed from JavaScript, you should keep that option disabled.'=>'If your PHP scripts send cookies that need to be accessed from JavaScript, you should keep that option disabled.','Adding this flag to cookies helps to mitigate the risk of cross-site scripting by preventing them from being accessed through client-side scripts. NinjaFirewall can hook all cookies sent by your blog, its plugins or any other PHP script, add the <code>HttpOnly</code> flag if it is missing, and re-inject those cookies back into your server HTTP response headers right before they are sent to your visitors. Note that WordPress sets that flag on the logged in user cookies only.'=>'Adding this flag to cookies helps to mitigate the risk of cross-site scripting by preventing them from being accessed through client-side scripts. NinjaFirewall can hook all cookies sent by your blog, its plugins, or any other PHP script, add the <code>HttpOnly</code> flag, if it is missing, and re-inject those cookies back into your server HTTP response headers, right before they are sent to your visitors. Note that WordPress sets that flag on the logged in user cookies only.','Force <code>HttpOnly</code> flag on all cookies to mitigate XSS attacks'=>'Force <code>HttpOnly</code> flag on all cookies to mitigate XSS attacks','Since v3.1.3, WordPress sets this value to <code>SAMEORIGIN</code> for the administrator and the login page only.'=>'Since v3.1.3, WordPress sets this value to <code>SAMEORIGIN</code> for the administrator and the login page only.','NinjaFirewall does not support the <code>ALLOW-FROM</code> value.'=>'NinjaFirewall does not support the <code>ALLOW-FROM</code> value.','A browser receiving content with this header must not display this content in any frame.'=>'A browser receiving content with this header must not display this content in any frame.','A browser receiving content with this header must not display this content in any frame from a page of different origin than the content itself.'=>'A browser receiving content with this header must not display this content in any frame from a page of different origin than the content itself.','This header indicates a policy whether a browser must not allow to render a page in a &lt;frame&gt; or &lt;iframe&gt;. Hosts can declare this policy in the header of their HTTP responses to prevent clickjacking attacks, by ensuring that their content is not embedded into other pages or frames. NinjaFirewall accepts two different values:'=>'This header indicates a policy whether a browser must not allow to render a page in a &lt;frame&gt; or &lt;iframe&gt;. Hosts can declare this policy in the header of their HTTP responses to prevent clickjacking attacks, by ensuring that their content is not embedded into other pages or frames. NinjaFirewall accepts two different values:','Set <code>X-Frame-Options</code> to protect against clickjacking attempts'=>'Set <code>X-Frame-Options</code> to protect against clickjacking attempts','Set <code>X-Content-Type-Options</code> to protect against MIME type confusion attacks'=>'Set <code>X-Content-Type-Options</code> to protect against MIME type confusion attacks','In addition to filtering incoming requests, NinjaFirewall can also hook the HTTP response in order to alter its headers. Those modifications can help to mitigate threats such as XSS, phishing and clickjacking attacks.'=>'In addition to filtering incoming requests, NinjaFirewall can also hook the HTTP response in order to alter its headers. Those modifications can help to mitigate threats such as XSS, phishing and clickjacking attacks.','HTTP response headers'=>'HTTP response headers','This option will block any <code>POST</code> request that does not have a Referrer header (<code>HTTP_REFERER</code> variable). If you need external applications to post to your scripts (e.g. Paypal IPN, WordPress WP-Cron...), you are advised to keep this option disabled otherwise they will likely be blocked. Note that <code>POST</code> requests are not required to have a Referrer header and, for that reason, this option is disabled by default.'=>'This option will block any <code>POST</code> request that does not have a Referrer header (<code>HTTP_REFERER</code> variable). If you need external applications to post to your scripts (eg Paypal IPN, WordPress WP-Cron...), you are advised to keep this option disabled, otherwise they will likely be blocked. Note that <code>POST</code> requests are not required to have a Referrer header and, for that reason, this option is disabled by default.','Block POST requests that do not have an <code>HTTP_REFERER</code> header'=>'Block POST requests that do not have an <code>HTTP_REFERER</code> header','Whether to scan and/or sanitise <code>HTTP_REFERER</code> requests.'=>'Whether to scan and/or sanitise <code>HTTP_REFERER</code> requests.','HTTP_REFERER server variable'=>'HTTP_REFERER server variable','Rejects some known bots, scanners and various malicious scripts attempting to access your blog.'=>'Rejects some known bots, scanners, and various malicious scripts attempting to access your blog.','Whether to scan and/or sanitise <code>HTTP_USER_AGENT</code> requests.'=>'Whether to scan and/or sanitise <code>HTTP_USER_AGENT</code> requests.','HTTP_USER_AGENT server variable'=>'HTTP_USER_AGENT server variable','Whether to scan and/or sanitise cookies.'=>'Whether to scan and/or sanitise cookies.','Cookies'=>'Cookies','Whether to sanitise the <code>REQUEST</code> variable.'=>'Whether to sanitise the <code>REQUEST</code> variable.','HTTP REQUEST variable'=>'HTTP REQUEST variable','NinjaFirewall will decode and scan base64 encoded values in order to detect obfuscated malicious code. This option is only available for the <code>POST</code> variable.'=>'NinjaFirewall will decode and scan base64 encoded values in order to detect obfuscated malicious code. This option is only available for the <code>POST</code> variable.','Decode Base64-encoded <code>POST</code> variable:'=>'Decode Base64-encoded <code>POST</code> variable:','Whether to scan and/or sanitise the <code>POST</code> variable.'=>'Whether to scan and/or sanitise the <code>POST</code> variable.','HTTP POST variable'=>'HTTP POST variable','Whether to scan and/or sanitise the <code>GET</code> variable.'=>'Whether to scan and/or sanitise the <code>GET</code> variable.','HTTP GET variable'=>'HTTP GET variable','Any character that is not a letter <code>a-zA-Z</code>, a digit <code>0-9</code>, a dot <code>.</code>, a hyphen <code>-</code> or an underscore <code>_</code> will be removed from the filename and replaced with the substitution character.'=>'Any character that is not a letter <code>a-zA-Z</code>, a digit <code>0-9</code>, a dot <code>.</code>, a hyphen <code>-</code> or an underscore <code>_</code> will be removed from the filename and replaced with the substitution character.','Whether to allow/disallow file uploads.'=>'Whether to allow/disallow file uploads.','Uploads'=>'Uploads','Whether to filter HTTP and/or HTTPS traffic'=>'Whether to filter HTTP and/or HTTPS traffic','Firewall Policies'=>'Firewall Policies','If you enabled <code>POST</code> requests sanitising, articles and messages posted by your visitors could be corrupted with excessive backslashes or substitution characters.'=>'If you enabled <code>POST</code> requests sanitising, articles and messages posted by your visitors could be corrupted with excessive backslashes or substitution characters.','This action will be performed when the filtering process is over, right before NinjaFirewall forwards the request to your PHP script.'=>'This action will be performed when the filtering process is over, right before NinjaFirewall forwards the request to your PHP script.','Scan: If anything suspicious is detected, NinjaFirewall will block the request and return an HTTP error code and message (defined in the "Firewall Options" page). The user request will fail and the connection will be closed immediately.'=>'Scan : if anything suspicious is detected, NinjaFirewall will block the request and return an HTTP error code and message (defined in the "Firewall Options" page). The user request will fail and the connection will be closed immediately.','You can choose to scan and reject dangerous content but also to sanitise requests and variables. Those two actions are different and can be combined together for better security.'=>'You can choose to scan and reject dangerous content, but also to sanitise requests and variables. Those two actions are different and can be combined together for better security.','Scan and Sanitise'=>'Scan and Sanitise','Keep in mind, however, that the Firewall Policies apply to any PHP scripts located inside the %s directory and its sub-directories, and not only to your WordPress index page.'=>'Keep in mind, however, that the Firewall Policies apply to any PHP scripts located inside the %s directory and its sub-directories, and not only to your WordPress index page.','Use the options below to enable, disable or to tweak these rules according to your needs.'=>'Use the options below to enable, disable or to tweak these rules according to your needs.','Because NinjaFirewall sits in front of WordPress, it can hook, scan and sanitise all PHP requests, HTTP variables, headers and IPs before they reach your blog: <code><a href="%s">$_GET</a></code>, <code><a href="%s">$_POST</a></code>, <code><a href="%s">$_COOKIE</a></code>, <code><a href="%s">$_REQUEST</a></code>, <code><a href="%s">$_FILES</a></code>, <code><a href="%s">$_SERVER</a></code> in HTTP and/or HTTPS mode.'=>'Because NinjaFirewall sits in front of WordPress, it can hook, scan and sanitise all PHP requests, HTTP variables, headers and IPs before they reach your blog: <code><a href="%s">$_GET</a></code>, <code><a href="%s">$_POST</a></code>, <code><a href="%s">$_COOKIE</a></code>, <code><a href="%s">$_REQUEST</a></code>, <code><a href="%s">$_FILES</a></code>, <code><a href="%s">$_SERVER</a></code> in HTTP and/or HTTPS mode.','Policies overview'=>'Policies overview','"File Check" configuration will not be exported/imported.'=>'"File Check" configuration will not be exported/imported.','This options lets you export you current configuration or import it from another NinjaFirewall (WP Edition) installation. The imported file must match the major version of your current version (%s) otherwise it will be rejected. Note that importing will override all firewall rules and options.'=>'This options lets you export your current configuration or import it from another NinjaFirewall (WP Edition) installation. The imported file must match the major version of your current version (%s), otherwise it will be rejected. Note that importing will override all firewall rules and options.','Export/import configuration'=>'Export/import configuration','NinjaFirewall logo.'=>'NinjaFirewall logo.','the unique incident number as it will appear in the firewall log "INCIDENT" column.'=>'the unique incident number as it will appear in the firewall log "INCIDENT" column.','the blocked user IP.'=>'the blocked user IP.','You can use any HTML tags and 3 built-in variables:'=>'You can use any HTML tags and 3 built-in variables:','Lets you customize the HTTP error code returned by NinjaFirewall when blocking a dangerous request and the message to display to the user.'=>'Lets you customise the HTTP error code returned by NinjaFirewall when blocking a dangerous request and the message to display to the user.','We recommend to run it in Debugging Mode for at least 24 hours after installing it on a new site and then to keep an eye on the firewall log during that time. If you notice a false positive in the log, you can simply use NinjaFirewall\'s Rules Editor to disable the security rule that was wrongly triggered.'=>'We recommend to run it in Debugging Mode for at least 24 hours after installing it on a new site and then to keep an eye on the firewall log during that time. If you notice a false positive in the log, you can simply use NinjaFirewall\'s Rules Editor to disable the security rule that was wrongly triggered.','In Debugging mode, NinjaFirewall will not block or sanitise suspicious requests but will only log them. The <a href="%s">Firewall Log</a> will display <code>DEBUG_ON</code> in the LEVEL column.'=>'In Debugging mode, NinjaFirewall will not block or sanitise suspicious requests but will only log them. The <a href="%s">Firewall Log</a> will display <code>DEBUG_ON</code> in the LEVEL column.','Debugging mode'=>'Debugging mode','Your site will remain unprotected until you enable it again.'=>'Your site will remain unprotected until you enable it again.','This option allows you to disable NinjaFirewall. It has basically the same effect as deactivating it from the <a href="%s">Plugins</a> menu page.'=>'This option allows you to disable NinjaFirewall. It has basically the same effect as deactivating it from the <a href="%s">Plugins</a> menu page.','Firewall protection'=>'Firewall protection','Benchmarks show the time NinjaFirewall took, in seconds, to process each request it has blocked.'=>'Benchmarks show the time NinjaFirewall took, in seconds, to proceed each request it has blocked.','Benchmarks'=>'Benchmarks','You can view the log by clicking on the <a href="%s">Firewall Log</a> menu.'=>'You can view the log by clicking on the <a href="%s">Firewall Log</a> menu.','Statistics are taken from the current log. It is rotated on the first day of each month.'=>'Statistics are taken from the current log. It is rotated on the first day of each month.','This is NinjaFirewall Dashboard page; it shows information about the firewall status. We recommend you keep an eye on it because, in case of problems, all possible errors and warnings will be displayed here.'=>'This is the NinjaFirewall Dashboard page; it shows information about the firewall status. We recommend you keep an eye on it because, in case of problems, all possible errors and warnings will be displayed here.']];